WEBVTT

00:01.479 --> 00:03.133
<i>- Previously
on "Superman & Lois"...</i>

00:03.177 --> 00:05.831
<i>- Let's just focus on what
we came here for--family.</i>

00:05.875 --> 00:08.182
- You and Jordan
basically are weapons.

00:08.225 --> 00:11.315
I'm the only one in this house
that is completely unarmed.

00:11.359 --> 00:13.578
- You don't go
snooping around

00:13.622 --> 00:15.928
some guy from another world's
murder van.

00:15.972 --> 00:19.845
We are the extraordinary humans
in a family of super people.

00:19.889 --> 00:21.369
<i>- Have you seen my dad?</i>

00:21.412 --> 00:22.805
I can't do the performance
without him.

00:22.848 --> 00:24.154
- I can do it.

00:24.198 --> 00:25.373
- I can't keep getting
my hopes up

00:25.416 --> 00:26.896
and then just get disappointed.

00:26.939 --> 00:28.811
- Were you able to find
enough Subjekts?

00:28.854 --> 00:31.118
- Yes, but there's no guarantee
they'll be receptive hosts.

00:31.161 --> 00:32.858
<i>- That was a nasty sight.</i>

00:32.902 --> 00:35.905
- The gas was an experimental
synthetic kryptonite

00:35.948 --> 00:38.081
designed to invade
your respiratory system,

00:38.125 --> 00:39.778
weaken you from the inside.

00:44.174 --> 00:51.225
<i>♪</i>

00:58.101 --> 01:00.538
- Why is Edge here?

01:00.582 --> 01:04.194
I mean, why Smallville?

01:04.238 --> 01:06.544
- Definitely not
for the biryani.

01:06.588 --> 01:09.852
- He was in and out of Hazel
Green and Granville in weeks,

01:09.895 --> 01:12.115
he shut down operations in
New Carthage in a few months,

01:12.159 --> 01:13.986
and now he's here.

01:14.030 --> 01:16.424
- Gotta be for the same reason
as the other towns, right?

01:16.467 --> 01:18.121
Mine for X-Kryptonite,

01:18.165 --> 01:20.297
use that machine I saw
that gives people powers.

01:20.341 --> 01:22.169
- Yeah,
I know that's part of it,

01:22.212 --> 01:24.910
but Smallville's the only town
where he's sticking around,

01:24.954 --> 01:28.131
so there has to be a reason
why Smallville is different.

01:28.175 --> 01:30.002
He needs this place.

01:30.046 --> 01:33.441
- This is your specialty.

01:33.484 --> 01:36.139
How do you suggest
we figure out why?

01:36.183 --> 01:37.880
- We dig deeper.

01:37.923 --> 01:40.883
<i>We need to use every resource
at our disposal.</i>

01:40.926 --> 01:43.364
So as we know, he was only
in Hazel Green...

01:43.407 --> 01:45.409
<i>Clark's a great reporter.</i>

01:45.453 --> 01:48.717
<i>Now that he's not coaching,
he can help.</i>

01:48.760 --> 01:52.590
<i>We get all the information
we can from Lana,</i>

01:52.634 --> 01:57.029
<i>files on everyone
Edge has recruited,</i>

01:57.073 --> 02:00.163
<i>who they are,
where they come from.</i>

02:00.207 --> 02:01.643
- Thank you.

02:01.686 --> 02:04.254
<i>- Pore over
every single detail.</i>

02:04.298 --> 02:05.647
<i>♪</i>

02:05.690 --> 02:07.388
There's Emily.

02:07.431 --> 02:09.303
<i>And then we start back
at the beginning.</i>

02:09.346 --> 02:11.914
- All right, so we know
Emily is the newest recruit.

02:11.957 --> 02:16.875
<i>- Connect every dot,
piece it all together,</i>

02:16.919 --> 02:19.530
<i>and if we've
done our job right,</i>

02:19.574 --> 02:22.577
<i>the answer will
present itself.</i>

02:22.620 --> 02:24.709
<i>- My goal has always been
the same.</i>

02:24.753 --> 02:27.495
I want to change this world,

02:27.538 --> 02:31.063
and I finally found the place
where I can start doing so--

02:31.107 --> 02:34.763
here in Smallville
with people like you.

02:34.806 --> 02:36.808
- Me?

02:36.852 --> 02:38.506
Why?

02:38.549 --> 02:41.857
- I know your life hasn't been
easy the past few years.

02:41.900 --> 02:44.076
I know the pain you're in.

02:44.120 --> 02:46.253
<i>♪</i>

02:46.296 --> 02:48.429
<i>The fear,</i>

02:48.472 --> 02:50.561
<i>knowing you can't provide
for your family,</i>

02:50.605 --> 02:55.610
<i>that burden, that stress.</i>

02:55.653 --> 02:57.699
<i>With my assistance,
all those fears can go away.</i>

02:57.742 --> 03:01.877
I can improve your life
in every way imaginable.

03:01.920 --> 03:04.749
<i>I can improve you, Emily.</i>

03:04.793 --> 03:06.186
- Will this hurt?

03:10.973 --> 03:13.410
- Not a bit.

03:16.326 --> 03:20.374
<i>- If you'd like me to,
I can activate a new life.</i>

03:20.417 --> 03:22.854
- A new life?

03:22.898 --> 03:24.987
- Process you'd go through
will make you feel

03:25.030 --> 03:26.858
like a new person,

03:26.902 --> 03:30.558
<i>clear-minded, stronger,</i>

03:30.601 --> 03:34.083
<i>capable of things
you never dreamt possible.</i>

03:34.126 --> 03:38.000
But I can only do that
if you're willing,

03:38.043 --> 03:42.265
<i>if you acknowledge
that the life you have now</i>

03:42.309 --> 03:44.136
<i>is not what you want anymore.</i>

03:44.180 --> 03:47.139
- Complete host acceptance.

03:49.925 --> 03:51.666
- Process isn't complete.

03:51.709 --> 03:53.972
It'll take a few days
before you're fully in control,

03:54.016 --> 03:56.236
but once that happens...

03:58.890 --> 04:02.416
Life will be yours again.

04:02.459 --> 04:08.335
Do you want to become
your best self, Emily?

04:08.378 --> 04:09.597
- I do.

04:09.640 --> 04:16.691
<i>♪</i>

04:18.519 --> 04:22.000
<i>- Lana said Edge asked her
to find more candidates,</i>

04:22.044 --> 04:24.089
so until we can figure out
how to stop him,

04:24.133 --> 04:26.570
we need to convince people
to stay away.

04:26.614 --> 04:29.399
- Lois, he's offering people
jobs and money,

04:29.443 --> 04:32.010
things they need to feel in
control of their lives again.

04:32.054 --> 04:33.969
Boys, bus'll be here
in a minute!

04:34.012 --> 04:35.318
- Clark,
we have to do something,

04:35.362 --> 04:36.841
and nobody's gonna listen
to me.

04:36.885 --> 04:38.147
They haven't
since that first town hall,

04:38.190 --> 04:39.366
but they will to you.

04:39.409 --> 04:41.324
- Hey, which one's mine?
- Here.

04:41.368 --> 04:42.847
- Thanks.

04:42.891 --> 04:44.414
- All right, guys,
we're probably gonna have

04:44.458 --> 04:45.894
another late night working
on this Edge case.

04:45.937 --> 04:47.591
- All right,

04:47.635 --> 04:50.899
- We were gonna see
Sarah's revue tonight anyway.

04:50.942 --> 04:53.162
- You guys sure are spending
quite a bit of time together

04:53.205 --> 04:55.295
for just being "friends."

04:55.338 --> 04:57.166
- Just trying to support her,
Dad.

04:57.209 --> 04:59.168
- Uh-huh.
- Right.

05:00.648 --> 05:01.997
- What?

05:02.040 --> 05:03.825
She said she just wanted
to be friends.

05:03.868 --> 05:05.957
- Might be more than that,
but I will leave it up to her

05:06.001 --> 05:08.960
to tell you.

05:09.004 --> 05:11.136
- Bus is pulling up.

05:11.180 --> 05:12.790
- All right, there's leftovers
in the fridge, okay?

05:12.834 --> 05:14.401
- All right, love you guys.
Bye.

05:14.444 --> 05:17.055
- All right, I gotta go
meet Lana at the Gazette.

05:17.099 --> 05:19.971
Clark,
you are Martha Kent's son.

05:20.015 --> 05:22.800
She was helping people here
way before Edge showed up.

05:22.844 --> 05:25.020
They will listen to you.

05:25.063 --> 05:26.587
- All right.

05:26.630 --> 05:28.328
- Bye.
- Bye.

05:31.069 --> 05:34.072
- And none of these people are
acting differently at all?

05:34.116 --> 05:38.207
- I mean, the only change I see
is how happy they are.

05:38.250 --> 05:41.036
Like, they're truly excited
to be there,

05:41.079 --> 05:44.126
to be a part of something,
to change their lives.

05:44.169 --> 05:45.910
- What is he doing with them?

05:45.954 --> 05:48.478
- Personal development,
self-improvement,

05:48.522 --> 05:50.393
trust exercises.

05:50.437 --> 05:52.613
I really don't know
the specifics.

05:52.656 --> 05:54.354
- Well, it sounds like a cult,

05:54.397 --> 05:57.095
only Edge is power-brainwashing
free of charge.

05:57.139 --> 05:59.402
- The only other thing
I can tell you

05:59.446 --> 06:03.058
is they started these morning
"togethers" at Victoria May's.

06:03.101 --> 06:04.712
- Togethers?
- Mm-hmm.

06:04.755 --> 06:08.672
Camaraderie-building
breakfasts.

06:08.716 --> 06:10.413
Oh, I'm gonna be late.

06:10.457 --> 06:12.894
- Wait--Lana,
maybe you should take a break.

06:12.937 --> 06:15.026
This is kinda starting
to get really dangerous,

06:15.070 --> 06:16.593
and I don't want anything
to happen to you.

06:16.637 --> 06:18.943
- It's okay, Lois, really.

06:18.987 --> 06:22.947
I mean, if I can keep Edge
from hurting just one person,

06:22.991 --> 06:24.688
it's worth it.

06:26.951 --> 06:28.605
- Think I should head over
to the diner,

06:28.649 --> 06:30.694
go full intervention
on this breakfast.

06:30.738 --> 06:33.001
- No, you stay focused
on getting what you can

06:33.044 --> 06:35.003
on Edge's minions.

06:35.046 --> 06:38.920
I know someone who might have a
better shot at getting through.

06:43.446 --> 06:46.797
<i>♪</i>

06:46.841 --> 06:48.669
- Okay.

06:48.712 --> 06:50.453
Hey, boys!

06:50.497 --> 06:52.934
Hey, come on over.

06:52.977 --> 06:54.892
- Hey, Mr. Cushing.
- Hi.

06:54.936 --> 06:57.199
- Jordan, listen, I...

06:57.242 --> 06:59.201
I just want to say thank you
for stepping up

06:59.244 --> 07:01.116
and helping Sarah with
her audition the other day.

07:01.159 --> 07:03.858
That really saved the day, man.

07:03.901 --> 07:05.773
- Yeah, uh, thanks.

07:05.816 --> 07:07.688
- Okay, you don't want
to be late.

07:07.731 --> 07:09.820
- Yeah.

07:09.864 --> 07:11.996
- Hey, we'll see you later,
okay?

07:12.040 --> 07:13.563
- Yeah.

07:13.607 --> 07:15.783
- Can't wait to see you
up there tonight!

07:15.826 --> 07:17.393
- Don't ask.

07:17.437 --> 07:19.308
He's having some kind
of personality crisis.

07:19.351 --> 07:21.005
- Really?

07:21.049 --> 07:22.659
- Yeah, he keeps telling me
how he's changed for good

07:22.703 --> 07:24.531
and how he feels better.

07:24.574 --> 07:26.707
Things improve for a little bit,
it's the same crap as always,

07:26.750 --> 07:29.797
and then he crashes
like your brother's about to.

07:29.840 --> 07:31.407
- What?

07:31.451 --> 07:33.148
- I told you, stay away
from Tegan Wickhem.

07:33.191 --> 07:35.803
Just trust me, okay?

07:38.849 --> 07:45.900
<i>♪</i>

07:54.256 --> 07:55.953
- Clark?

07:55.997 --> 07:57.259
- Emily, hi.

07:57.302 --> 07:58.782
- I heard you were back
in town.

07:58.826 --> 08:00.567
- Yeah, I'm sorry I haven't
seen you.

08:00.610 --> 08:02.786
It's been crazy
since we moved here.

08:02.830 --> 08:05.876
- I bet--me, too, actually,
but for the better.

08:05.920 --> 08:07.269
- Oh, yeah?

08:07.312 --> 08:09.358
I heard you were working
at Edge EnerCorp.

08:09.401 --> 08:12.535
- It has changed my life.

08:14.406 --> 08:16.060
I feel great.

08:16.104 --> 08:18.498
I can think better, focus,
you know,

08:18.541 --> 08:21.762
problems that seemed impossible
before are like nothing now.

08:21.805 --> 08:23.503
- Really?
Wow, you know what?

08:23.546 --> 08:25.243
Actually, I would love to talk
to you about that.

08:25.287 --> 08:26.897
- Like, you're looking
for work?

08:26.941 --> 08:28.856
- Uh, well--
- Oh, it's okay.

08:28.899 --> 08:30.422
Just talk to Lana.

08:30.466 --> 08:32.903
She hooked me up,
got me into the program.

08:32.947 --> 08:36.037
I'm sure she'd be happy
to help her old boyfriend.

08:36.080 --> 08:38.648
- Yeah.
- Oh, I gotta go.

08:38.692 --> 08:40.345
Let me know
if I can be of help.

08:40.389 --> 08:42.130
It was so good to see you,
Clark.

08:42.173 --> 08:44.088
- You, too.
- Take care.

08:53.315 --> 08:56.753
<i>♪</i>

09:00.322 --> 09:07.372
<i>♪</i>

09:12.464 --> 09:15.511
<i>-</i>

09:29.177 --> 09:34.965
<i>♪</i>

10:02.776 --> 10:09.826
<i>♪</i>

10:17.834 --> 10:24.885
<i>♪</i>

10:46.210 --> 10:53.261
<i>♪</i>

10:55.045 --> 10:56.699
- Thank God you're back.

10:56.743 --> 10:59.180
Edge just sent someone over
with a massive ad buy

10:59.223 --> 11:01.095
for tomorrow's paper.

11:01.138 --> 11:04.098
- For more recruits?
- Twice as many.

11:04.141 --> 11:07.057
Whatever crazy voodoo
Edge is doing to those people,

11:07.101 --> 11:08.929
he's kicking it into high gear.

11:08.972 --> 11:11.453
Where are you going?

11:11.496 --> 11:13.803
- Oh, to make a scene.

11:13.847 --> 11:18.982
<i>♪</i>

11:19.026 --> 11:20.331
- Lois.
- Where's Edge?

11:20.375 --> 11:21.898
- He's in a group meeting.

11:21.942 --> 11:24.422
I just found out about the ad
this morning.

11:24.466 --> 11:27.512
<i>♪</i>

11:27.556 --> 11:29.514
- You don't want anything
to do with what he's offering.

11:29.558 --> 11:31.038
- Ms. Lane--

11:31.081 --> 11:32.735
- You all need to walk away
right now.

11:32.779 --> 11:35.085
Walk away.

11:35.129 --> 11:37.000
Don't touch me.

11:37.044 --> 11:39.437
- I'm sorry, if everyone could
give Ms. Lane and I a moment.

11:39.481 --> 11:40.961
I promise this won't take long.

11:41.004 --> 11:43.180
- I know this sounds insane
because it is,

11:43.224 --> 11:45.835
but he wants to erase
everything you are

11:45.879 --> 11:48.229
and replace it
with something else.

11:52.799 --> 11:54.409
- Well, that was desperate.

11:54.452 --> 11:56.541
- I know what you're doing.

11:56.585 --> 11:59.109
- Providing good jobs
to a community in need.

11:59.153 --> 12:01.459
- You are putting
Kryptonian consciousnesses

12:01.503 --> 12:03.026
into people's bodies.

12:03.070 --> 12:06.595
You are taking them over
and giving them powers.

12:06.638 --> 12:09.076
- And your evidence
for this is...

12:09.119 --> 12:12.166
- Derek Powell, Reno Rosetti,
Leslie.

12:12.209 --> 12:15.386
- Oh, so two dead men
and my personal assistant.

12:15.430 --> 12:18.999
I have to say, this story has
holes even by your standards.

12:19.042 --> 12:21.175
- We both know it's the truth.

12:21.218 --> 12:24.004
- In my experience,
truth is rather subjective.

12:24.047 --> 12:25.832
- Who do you think people are
more likely to believe?

12:25.875 --> 12:29.139
A has-been slumming it
at the local paper

12:29.183 --> 12:30.358
or the man
who's giving this town

12:30.401 --> 12:32.055
the best economy
it's ever known?

12:32.099 --> 12:35.624
- These people are not puppets
to be controlled by you.

12:35.667 --> 12:38.583
They have dreams.
They have families.

12:38.627 --> 12:41.282
- No one's being forced to do
anything against their will.

12:41.325 --> 12:44.111
the chance for a better life.

12:44.154 --> 12:46.809
Says so right there.
- We're not publishing this.

12:46.853 --> 12:50.595
- Then I guess word of mouth
will have to suffice.

12:50.639 --> 12:54.251
You can't stop this, Lois.

12:54.295 --> 12:56.253
Perhaps it's time you use
that device you have

12:56.297 --> 12:58.734
to call in your super friend.

12:58.778 --> 13:02.259
- Perhaps it is.

13:02.303 --> 13:03.957
- Risky, though.

13:04.000 --> 13:06.307
Need I remind you
where he's from?

13:06.350 --> 13:08.352
He may take comfort knowing
there are others here

13:08.396 --> 13:10.833
just like him,

13:10.877 --> 13:13.836
as John Irons prophesied.

13:13.880 --> 13:16.534
- Superman is nothing
like them.

13:19.102 --> 13:21.191
I'm excited to find out.

13:21.235 --> 13:27.807
<i>♪</i>

13:29.852 --> 13:31.941
- Hey, looks like you finally
figured out that locker.

13:31.985 --> 13:34.030
- Yeah, no, yeah,
I took your advice.

13:34.074 --> 13:36.641
You know, nothing good
ever comes from anger, so...

13:39.688 --> 13:42.125
<i>♪</i>

13:42.169 --> 13:44.519
- Hey, Tegan.

13:44.562 --> 13:48.871
Hey, um, I was just wondering
if, like, maybe you wanted

13:48.915 --> 13:52.701
to, like,
hang out after school sometime?

13:52.744 --> 13:54.659
- Hang out?

13:54.703 --> 13:57.488
Like, just the two of us?
- Yeah, I mean,

13:57.532 --> 14:01.101
it doesn't have to be, like,
that formal or anything, just,

14:01.144 --> 14:03.407
I don't know,
grab a bite at the diner, or...

14:03.451 --> 14:06.584
- Um...

14:06.628 --> 14:09.674
Look, I'm sure you're
a really sweet guy and all...

14:09.718 --> 14:11.938
- Look, I just--I thought--

14:11.981 --> 14:14.766
I don't know, I just thought,
like, we were trading looks.

14:14.810 --> 14:18.596
- Well, yeah, I mean,
you had that broken arm,

14:18.640 --> 14:19.902
and you looked so lonely.

14:19.946 --> 14:22.992
I was just trying to be nice.

14:23.036 --> 14:24.907
- Yeah, right.

14:24.951 --> 14:26.517
- Look, I wasn't trying to hurt
your feelings or anything--

14:26.561 --> 14:28.911
- No, no, no, no, no, no,
it's, uh...

14:28.955 --> 14:30.217
it's all good.

14:30.260 --> 14:32.523
It's my bad.

14:32.567 --> 14:35.004
- Cool.
- See ya later.

14:35.048 --> 14:37.441
<i>♪</i>

14:37.485 --> 14:40.618
- Whew, looks like you need
a new playbook, QB number two.

14:40.662 --> 14:42.446
You gotta work
on closing that deal

14:42.490 --> 14:44.753
like you close your locker.

14:44.796 --> 14:49.497
<i>♪</i>

14:49.540 --> 14:51.499
- Clark, are you here?
- In the kitchen.

14:51.542 --> 14:53.109
- We got a problem.

14:53.153 --> 14:55.895
Morgan Edge is ramping up
that program of his.

14:55.938 --> 14:58.462
Oh, my God, what happened?

14:58.506 --> 14:59.463
- I went to stop
this bank robbery,

14:59.507 --> 15:01.117
and I got hit.

15:01.161 --> 15:03.641
- Did they use kryptonite?
- No, regular bullets.

15:03.685 --> 15:05.295
- This isn't normal.

15:05.339 --> 15:08.037
Superman doesn't bruise,
especially not from bullets.

15:08.081 --> 15:09.604
- Do you think it has something
to do with that gas

15:09.647 --> 15:10.953
Rosetti used?

15:10.997 --> 15:12.215
- I don't know.

15:12.259 --> 15:13.782
We're gonna have
to call my dad.

15:18.265 --> 15:21.007
- Sorry about messing up
the intro.

15:21.050 --> 15:24.924
- I didn't even notice.
You sounded great.

15:24.967 --> 15:27.796
- Thanks.

15:27.839 --> 15:29.667
How are you so awesome
at piano?

15:29.711 --> 15:31.191
Do you have any other little

15:31.234 --> 15:32.670
secret talents
you're not telling me about?

15:32.714 --> 15:34.672
- Um...

15:34.716 --> 15:37.327
nah, this is pretty much it.
-

15:37.371 --> 15:40.461
Well, thank you
for everything,

15:40.504 --> 15:43.333
all the time you've put
into this.

15:43.377 --> 15:45.901
It really means a lot
having you here, so...

15:48.164 --> 15:49.774
- I want to be here.

15:52.777 --> 15:54.736
<i>♪</i>

15:58.348 --> 16:00.394
- Bless you.

16:00.437 --> 16:02.439
<i>♪</i>

16:02.483 --> 16:06.617
- I, um--I must have allergies
or something.

16:06.661 --> 16:09.577
- Jordan, I--

16:09.620 --> 16:11.579
Jordan!

16:11.622 --> 16:16.410
<i>♪</i>

16:26.811 --> 16:29.031
- Jordan.

16:29.075 --> 16:30.641
<i>♪</i>

16:30.685 --> 16:32.513
- Something's wrong with me.

16:32.556 --> 16:34.950
<i>♪</i>

16:34.994 --> 16:37.257
- You're infected, too.

16:37.300 --> 16:38.736
Come on.

16:38.780 --> 16:40.260
<i>♪</i>

16:44.046 --> 16:45.830
- Here, honey.
- So what's happening?

16:45.874 --> 16:48.311
- The kryptonite gas that
Rosetti used on me at the DOD,

16:48.355 --> 16:51.314
it was a bio-weapon, and I think
it might be communicable.

16:51.358 --> 16:55.057
- Like, a virus?

16:55.101 --> 17:00.323
So I'm getting
kryptonite sickness from you?

17:00.367 --> 17:02.064
- Yeah.

17:02.108 --> 17:03.892
- Clark, it's not your fault.

17:03.935 --> 17:06.590
You didn't even know anything
was happening until today.

17:06.634 --> 17:09.811
- You have super-healing,
so how long are you sick for?

17:09.854 --> 17:13.249
- Your dad has never been sick
a day in his life.

17:14.729 --> 17:18.167
- Well, I'm not that bad.

17:21.040 --> 17:24.043
Ow.

17:24.086 --> 17:25.870
- This wasn't supposed
to happen.

17:25.914 --> 17:27.698
- Really?

17:27.742 --> 17:30.701
Because it sure seems like a
weapon designed to hurt Superman

17:30.745 --> 17:32.790
would hurt Superman.

17:32.834 --> 17:34.966
- It was only meant
as a last resort,

17:35.010 --> 17:37.360
just to weaken him temporarily.

17:37.404 --> 17:40.798
- Then why is my son sick?
Explain that to me.

17:40.842 --> 17:43.714
You put your own grandson
in harm's way.

17:43.758 --> 17:46.239
- Sam, how do we fix this?

17:46.282 --> 17:48.502
- My guys are working on it.

17:50.634 --> 17:53.115
- Yo, Sarah.
- Hi.

17:53.159 --> 17:54.986
- Hey, are there gonna
be, like, refreshments

17:55.030 --> 17:56.771
at this thing, or what?

17:56.814 --> 17:58.294
- Have you seen Jordan?

17:58.338 --> 17:59.643
- No, he's probably
just, like, putting on

17:59.687 --> 18:01.080
his best black tee
for the show.

18:01.123 --> 18:02.429
You know how it goes.
- No, I don't,

18:02.472 --> 18:04.126
because he left
about an hour ago,

18:04.170 --> 18:05.519
and he hasn't come back.

18:05.562 --> 18:06.911
- Did he tell you
where he was going?

18:06.955 --> 18:08.261
- No, he just
ran out of rehearsal

18:08.304 --> 18:10.785
like a frightened
little rabbit, I...

18:10.828 --> 18:13.831
We were really having
a nice time together,

18:13.875 --> 18:16.182
or at least I thought we were
until he completely ghosted me.

18:16.225 --> 18:17.879
- Sarah, I don't think
it's about you.

18:17.922 --> 18:19.794
I'll find him.

18:19.837 --> 18:22.753
- Okay, well, hurry up because
I think I'm the first one up.

18:22.797 --> 18:24.712
- All right.

18:26.496 --> 18:28.194
- Emily.

18:28.237 --> 18:29.891
Emily, hey.

18:29.934 --> 18:31.936
I've been meaning to ask you,

18:31.980 --> 18:34.722
how's it going
with the program?

18:34.765 --> 18:37.812
- Mr. Edge is a genius.

18:37.855 --> 18:40.119
You know, that he somehow
figured out a process

18:40.162 --> 18:42.164
to completely transform
people's lives,

18:42.208 --> 18:44.297
it's amazing.

18:44.340 --> 18:45.820
- What process?

18:45.863 --> 18:47.561
<i>♪</i>

18:47.604 --> 18:50.694
- I'm sorry, I assumed
you'd already gone through it.

18:50.738 --> 18:52.783
- No, I haven't.

18:52.827 --> 18:55.830
What did he do to you exactly?

18:55.873 --> 18:58.789
- Mr. Edge was very clear
we not tell anyone.

18:58.833 --> 19:02.184
- Emily, we've known each other
since the fifth grade.

19:02.228 --> 19:03.925
You can trust me.

19:03.968 --> 19:06.449
- Lana, do you have a moment?

19:06.493 --> 19:08.190
<i>♪</i>

19:08.234 --> 19:10.540
- I'll see you later.

19:10.584 --> 19:17.634
<i>♪</i>

19:21.899 --> 19:24.250
- It seems

19:24.293 --> 19:27.209
you've been looking into things
that don't concern you.

19:29.429 --> 19:32.345
- You put me in charge
of the Young Executive Program.

19:32.388 --> 19:35.217
I should at least know
what it's really about.

19:35.261 --> 19:38.568
- And is this to satisfy
your own curiosity

19:38.612 --> 19:41.136
or so that you can run
and tell Lois Lane?

19:41.180 --> 19:44.313
- I never told her anything.
- It's okay.

19:44.357 --> 19:46.141
As evidenced
by today's spectacle,

19:46.185 --> 19:47.534
Miss Lane is desperate.

19:47.577 --> 19:49.188
In fact, I'd have been
more surprised

19:49.231 --> 19:52.147
if she hadn't tried
to scare you into helping.

19:52.191 --> 19:54.105
<i>♪</i>

19:54.149 --> 19:59.372
- Emily told me about a process
she went under.

19:59.415 --> 20:02.331
What is she talking about?

20:02.375 --> 20:04.768
- An offer I made her,

20:04.812 --> 20:09.904
the same one I'm about to make
right now to you,

20:09.947 --> 20:13.647
and make no mistake.

20:13.690 --> 20:17.259
The answer you give will
impact the rest of your life.

20:17.303 --> 20:21.220
<i>♪</i>

20:21.263 --> 20:23.874
<i>- Jordan, where are you?
- Upstairs.</i>

20:25.789 --> 20:28.314
- Wow, it's like Iditarod-level
cold in here.

20:28.357 --> 20:30.272
- Your brother's sick.

20:30.316 --> 20:33.754
- Does that have something to
do with you flaking on Sarah?

20:33.797 --> 20:36.757
- I gotta get back there, I--
- You're not going anywhere.

20:36.800 --> 20:39.238
- Sarah's going on any minute,
and I can't just abandon her.

20:39.281 --> 20:41.152
- She'll be okay.
- No, she won't.

20:41.196 --> 20:42.806
This is exactly
what her dad did.

20:42.850 --> 20:44.199
I can't let that happen again.

20:44.243 --> 20:45.722
- I know you want
to be there for her,

20:45.766 --> 20:47.158
but you cannot go anywhere

20:47.202 --> 20:49.073
until we know exactly
what is going on.

20:49.117 --> 20:50.597
- Wait, w--wait, we don't even
know what's going on with him?

20:50.640 --> 20:51.946
- The kryptonite that infected
your brother

20:51.989 --> 20:53.426
is affecting him differently
than me.

20:53.469 --> 20:55.166
- Your grandfather's working
with the doctors

20:55.210 --> 20:56.385
to figure out
a way to help him.

20:56.429 --> 20:58.039
- Jonathan, he's gonna be fine.

21:01.651 --> 21:05.264
- Dad, that does not seem fine.

21:05.307 --> 21:07.178
- It's getting harder
to breathe.

21:07.222 --> 21:10.617
- What is happening to him?
- We can't wait for your dad.

21:10.660 --> 21:17.711
<i>♪</i>

21:18.973 --> 21:21.062
- Let me call you back.

21:23.282 --> 21:26.110
Why's Clark leaving?

21:26.154 --> 21:27.895
- To do what you can't.

21:27.938 --> 21:31.594
- Lois, that gas Rosetti used
on Clark was synthetic,

21:31.638 --> 21:33.770
experimental,
hadn't been tested.

21:33.814 --> 21:36.382
We didn't know
what his reaction would be.

21:40.299 --> 21:44.912
- All my life, your job was
your number one priority.

21:44.955 --> 21:47.958
Accepting that wasn't easy,

21:48.002 --> 21:50.744
but I learned to live with it,
and somehow even grew

21:50.787 --> 21:53.355
to respect it because I
believed that you were trying

21:53.399 --> 21:56.184
to do the right thing,
and I honestly naively thought

21:56.227 --> 21:59.622
that once I had a family,
you might change,

21:59.666 --> 22:02.625
start putting us first,

22:02.669 --> 22:05.585
but I was wrong.

22:05.628 --> 22:10.329
Knowingly and willingly
endangering the lives

22:10.372 --> 22:13.375
of the people I love--

22:13.419 --> 22:16.073
I can't forgive that.

22:16.117 --> 22:18.162
So when this is over,
I want you to leave

22:18.206 --> 22:20.382
and never come back.

22:23.429 --> 22:26.345
You're not welcome here
anymore.

22:26.388 --> 22:31.524
<i>♪</i>

22:37.530 --> 22:44.580
<i>♪</i>

22:46.234 --> 22:47.670
- Jordan's been infected
with kryptonite.

22:47.714 --> 22:49.063
It's affecting his breathing.

22:49.106 --> 22:51.282
<i>- He's
in respiratory distress.</i>

22:51.326 --> 22:53.328
- Why?

22:53.372 --> 22:56.113
<i>- The kryptonite is causing
his lungs to fill with fluid.</i>

22:56.157 --> 22:59.334
<i>As he can condense
large quantities of air--</i>

22:59.378 --> 23:01.945
- He's cooling it, like I do.

23:01.989 --> 23:03.730
Can you get the kryptonite
out of him?

23:03.773 --> 23:06.863
<i>- Likely, but only
the same way we have</i>

23:06.907 --> 23:09.039
<i>with you in the past.</i>

23:09.083 --> 23:15.872
<i>♪</i>

23:15.916 --> 23:18.135
- What?
- Come here.

23:18.179 --> 23:19.833
Come here.

23:19.876 --> 23:21.878
<i>♪</i>

23:21.922 --> 23:24.272
We're gonna have to burn the
kryptonite out of your system.

23:24.315 --> 23:27.318
- Burn it how?

23:27.362 --> 23:31.018
- With heat,
with some immense heat.

23:31.061 --> 23:32.933
- No, no--
- Listen to me, listen to me.

23:32.976 --> 23:34.848
Listen to me.
This is the only way, okay?

23:34.891 --> 23:36.458
We have to do this,

23:36.502 --> 23:38.025
otherwise your lungs
could completely freeze.

23:38.068 --> 23:40.680
- Dad, I'm scared.
- I'm gonna be right here.

23:40.723 --> 23:43.030
You're gonna take my hand,
okay?

23:43.073 --> 23:46.599
You're gonna squeeze as hard
as you need to, okay?

23:46.642 --> 23:48.514
You can do this.

23:48.557 --> 23:51.212
<i>♪</i>

23:58.045 --> 24:00.003
- Mom.

24:02.049 --> 24:04.660
Mom, you okay?

24:04.704 --> 24:07.228
- I should've protected him.

24:09.448 --> 24:11.798
Mom, this isn't--
this isn't on you.

24:15.323 --> 24:16.716
- I'm your mom.

24:16.759 --> 24:19.196
My one job
is to keep you guys safe,

24:19.240 --> 24:20.850
and I keep failing at it.

24:20.894 --> 24:22.852
- No, no, you don't.

24:22.896 --> 24:26.465
- You were almost gunned down
in John Henry's RV--

24:26.508 --> 24:29.076
- That was my fault.
- Got into a car accident.

24:29.119 --> 24:30.469
- That was also my fault.

24:30.512 --> 24:32.296
- I feel like
I can't turn around

24:32.340 --> 24:34.168
without one of you
being in mortal danger.

24:34.211 --> 24:37.214
Why is it so hard
to keep you safe?

24:39.129 --> 24:41.131
- I don't know.

24:41.175 --> 24:43.569
Just...

24:43.612 --> 24:47.703
Just part of being
a super family, I guess.

24:47.747 --> 24:51.141
<i>♪</i>

24:51.185 --> 24:53.709
Hey, come here.

24:53.753 --> 24:56.233
Dad'll figure something out.

24:56.277 --> 24:58.453
He always does.

24:58.497 --> 25:02.370
<i>♪</i>

25:05.416 --> 25:06.896
<i>♪</i>

25:06.940 --> 25:08.289
- Hey, Lana.
- Hey.

25:08.332 --> 25:10.639
- I saved you both seats.
- Oh, thank you.

25:10.683 --> 25:12.859
- Hi, how are you doing?
- Hey.

25:12.902 --> 25:14.469
Good to see you.

25:14.513 --> 25:18.908
<i>♪</i>

25:18.952 --> 25:21.563
- Hello, everyone,
and thank you for coming.

25:21.607 --> 25:22.912
Our students tonight...

25:22.956 --> 25:24.653
- How did everything go
with Edge?

25:24.697 --> 25:28.178
- Oh, amazing.
He explained everything to me.

25:28.222 --> 25:30.398
It all makes perfect sense.

25:30.441 --> 25:32.269
- All right.
- Yeah, thank you.

25:32.313 --> 25:34.358
- And for our first
performance,

25:34.402 --> 25:36.970
we have the very talented
Sarah Cushing

25:37.013 --> 25:39.625
singing "Little Light"
by Amos Lee.

25:39.668 --> 25:41.801
- Whoo!

25:49.852 --> 25:56.903
<i>♪</i>

25:58.165 --> 25:59.819
- Um...

25:59.862 --> 26:02.125
I'm sorry, I can't do this.

26:02.169 --> 26:05.085
- Yes, you can.

26:05.128 --> 26:07.304
It's just like being at home,
okay?

26:07.348 --> 26:14.355
<i>♪</i>

26:18.141 --> 26:25.192
<i>♪</i>

26:27.673 --> 26:33.113
- ♪ Some days I can't get
myself out of the box ♪

26:33.156 --> 26:38.509
♪ And some days I can't
find keys to any locks ♪

26:40.250 --> 26:45.908
♪ Some days I feel like
it's all overblown ♪

26:45.952 --> 26:50.957
♪ And then I look at you,
and I don't feel so alone ♪

26:51.000 --> 26:53.873
♪ And I say, hey

26:53.916 --> 27:00.662
♪ Let your little light shine

27:00.706 --> 27:04.797
♪ For the world to see

27:12.413 --> 27:19.463
<i>♪</i>

27:26.166 --> 27:28.037
- Just waiting to hear back
from my team.

27:28.081 --> 27:29.691
Then we'll get everything
straightened out

27:29.735 --> 27:31.258
with Jordan and your dad.

27:31.301 --> 27:33.173
- Little late for that,
isn't it?

27:35.741 --> 27:37.699
Why'd you do it?

27:39.614 --> 27:42.573
Why'd you build those weapons
to hurt my dad?

27:48.318 --> 27:51.626
- Your father's
the most powerful being

27:51.670 --> 27:54.411
this world's ever known.

27:54.455 --> 27:57.327
My job is to keep us safe,

27:57.371 --> 28:00.330
which means being prepared
for any scenario,

28:00.374 --> 28:03.856
no matter how unlikely.

28:03.899 --> 28:06.249
You and I,
we're not like your dad,

28:06.293 --> 28:08.469
or even Jordan.

28:08.512 --> 28:10.210
- He's my twin brother.

28:10.253 --> 28:14.736
- Yes, but the minute
his powers surfaced,

28:14.780 --> 28:18.348
you and him began walking
two very different paths.

28:20.524 --> 28:22.613
- That scares you, doesn't it?

28:22.657 --> 28:25.312
- It does.

28:26.922 --> 28:29.011
- You know,
I think you're wrong.

28:29.055 --> 28:32.406
I think you're wrong about
you and I being alike.

28:32.449 --> 28:34.321
- How so?

28:34.364 --> 28:36.410
<i>♪</i>

28:36.453 --> 28:40.501
- I could never be scared
of my family,

28:40.544 --> 28:42.459
no matter what powers
they might have.

28:42.503 --> 28:45.767
- Jonathan, you haven't
seen the things I have.

28:45.811 --> 28:47.769
<i>♪</i>

28:47.813 --> 28:49.945
- Yeah, you're right.

28:49.989 --> 28:52.382
<i>♪</i>

28:52.426 --> 28:54.733
But in the end,

28:54.776 --> 28:57.561
I don't think
that would matter

28:57.605 --> 28:59.999
'cause I'd still trust them,

29:00.042 --> 29:02.610
and you'd still be a coward.

29:02.653 --> 29:09.704
<i>♪</i>

29:13.621 --> 29:16.363
- ♪ There's a fight to be won

29:16.406 --> 29:19.453
♪ For the love
you find at home ♪

29:19.496 --> 29:22.630
- Mom.
- ♪ Words to be done for...

29:22.673 --> 29:26.112
- You were wonderful up there.
- Thank you.

29:26.155 --> 29:28.027
It felt really good
once I got going.

29:28.070 --> 29:30.594
- Yeah.
- Yeah, told you you'd kill it.

29:30.638 --> 29:34.860
- Thank you, Dad,
for helping me.

29:37.863 --> 29:40.213
- ♪ Well, I know I have...

29:46.262 --> 29:48.351
<i>♪</i>

29:48.395 --> 29:51.441
♪ Please forgive
if I don't walk... ♪

29:51.485 --> 29:54.053
- Emily, where are you going?
Avery's not done yet.

29:54.096 --> 29:55.489
- I'll be right back.

29:55.532 --> 29:59.232
<i>♪</i>

29:59.275 --> 30:02.670
- That was weird.
- Yeah.

30:02.713 --> 30:03.845
- I'm gonna go see
what's wrong.

30:03.889 --> 30:05.455
- Wait, Kyle--

30:05.499 --> 30:08.676
<i>♪</i>

30:08.719 --> 30:11.897
- Have you seen this?

30:11.940 --> 30:13.899
<i>♪</i>

30:13.942 --> 30:15.857
He's still weak.

30:15.901 --> 30:19.600
- The exact reason why I just
activated some of our Subjekts.

30:19.643 --> 30:22.211
- To take down Superman?

30:22.255 --> 30:24.779
- Not him,

30:24.823 --> 30:26.955
the one he protects.

30:26.999 --> 30:28.739
<i>♪</i>

30:32.265 --> 30:33.614
<i>- The kryptonite
is nearly gone.</i>

30:33.657 --> 30:35.355
- Doing great,
you're almost there.

30:35.398 --> 30:37.531
You're almost there.
-

30:39.402 --> 30:41.535
- That's it, that's it!
It's over.

30:41.578 --> 30:43.276
That's it, it's over.
You're done.

30:43.319 --> 30:45.278
Hey, you did it, okay?
Hey.

30:45.321 --> 30:47.236
Hey, I'm proud of you.

30:47.280 --> 30:49.673
You all right?
Come here.

30:49.717 --> 30:51.719
I'm proud of you.
Come on, stand up.

30:51.762 --> 30:53.852
Stand up.

30:53.895 --> 30:57.725
- What do you mean, you don't
know how long it'll affect him?

30:57.768 --> 31:00.902
No, I haven't tested
the prototype.

31:00.946 --> 31:03.165
He wasn't exactly in the mood.

31:03.209 --> 31:06.038
Just get me an answer.

31:09.084 --> 31:16.048
<i>♪</i>

31:16.091 --> 31:19.399
- Can we just, like--
like, call them or something?

31:19.442 --> 31:23.185
- It's named the Fortress
of Solitude for a reason.

31:23.229 --> 31:24.578
I know it sucks.

31:24.621 --> 31:27.624
We just have to be patient,
okay?

31:35.632 --> 31:36.938
Hey, Lana.

31:36.982 --> 31:39.158
- Lois, you know
how you kept asking me

31:39.201 --> 31:41.029
if anyone over
at Edge EnerCorp

31:41.073 --> 31:43.162
was acting differently?

31:43.205 --> 31:46.774
I just saw it for the first
time with Emily Phan.

31:46.817 --> 31:48.950
- Emily? <i>
- Yeah.</i>

31:48.994 --> 31:51.518
She left in the middle
of her daughter's performance.

31:51.561 --> 31:55.000
She would never do that.
Avery is everything to her.

31:55.043 --> 31:57.219
I mean, it's like she was--

31:57.263 --> 31:59.395
- She was someone else.

31:59.439 --> 32:00.962
<i>♪</i>

32:01.006 --> 32:03.965
- I'll get it.

32:04.009 --> 32:06.141
<i>- I guess this is
what Edge meant.</i>

32:06.185 --> 32:07.751
- What do you mean?

32:07.795 --> 32:09.579
<i>- Tonight
before I left the office,</i>

32:09.623 --> 32:11.538
he made me an offer

32:11.581 --> 32:13.627
to do what he's doing
to everyone else.

32:13.670 --> 32:16.282
- What?
- I turned him down.

32:16.325 --> 32:18.806
- Lana, why wouldn't you
mention this before?

32:18.849 --> 32:21.200
- 'Cause I was nervous.

32:21.243 --> 32:23.680
He knew I was feeding you
information.

32:23.724 --> 32:25.378
- Hey, Mom,
I think it's for you.

32:25.421 --> 32:28.033
<i>- Lois, I'm worried.</i>

32:28.076 --> 32:29.860
<i>What if he does something?</i>

32:32.907 --> 32:35.736
- Mom? <i>
- Lois?</i>

32:35.779 --> 32:37.956
- She shouldn't have called. <i>
- Lois.</i>

32:37.999 --> 32:45.006
<i>♪</i>

32:45.789 --> 32:48.488
- Not this time.

32:48.531 --> 32:50.403
- Ahh!

32:50.446 --> 32:52.361
<i>♪</i>

32:52.405 --> 32:54.494
This isn't you.

32:54.537 --> 32:57.105
- Not anymore.

32:57.149 --> 33:01.066
<i>♪</i>

33:01.109 --> 33:03.633
- Get out of here!
-

33:03.677 --> 33:05.026
- Keep hitting this
till he comes.

33:05.070 --> 33:06.680
It's all we can do.
- No, no, no, no.

33:06.723 --> 33:08.421
We need to go to the barn.
- I'll keep 'em busy.

33:08.464 --> 33:15.515
<i>♪</i>

33:21.173 --> 33:23.175
- You took his weapons?

33:23.218 --> 33:25.916
<i>♪</i>

33:25.960 --> 33:27.440
Kyle?

33:27.483 --> 33:28.832
- I just came
from the performance.

33:28.876 --> 33:31.444
Lana was scared.
What's going on?

33:31.487 --> 33:35.100
- Edge sent people to kill me.
- It's not gonna happen.

33:35.143 --> 33:38.538
<i>♪</i>

33:46.763 --> 33:49.070
- Stay down.

33:49.114 --> 33:56.121
<i>♪</i>

34:00.864 --> 34:03.476
- Targets first.

34:04.172 --> 34:07.654
- So that's what kryptonite
feels like, huh?

34:07.697 --> 34:09.569
- Yeah.

34:17.794 --> 34:19.666
- Dad?

34:22.712 --> 34:29.763
<i>♪</i>

34:30.894 --> 34:33.984
- I'm sorry, Jordan.

34:34.028 --> 34:35.856
Your life right now
is completely changed

34:35.899 --> 34:37.423
because of who I am.

34:39.425 --> 34:42.906
Everything that's happening
to you,

34:42.950 --> 34:44.995
you didn't ask for any of this.

34:45.039 --> 34:47.259
<i>♪</i>

34:47.302 --> 34:50.392
- I didn't,

34:50.436 --> 34:52.829
but you didn't ask for what
happened to you either.

34:52.873 --> 34:59.575
<i>♪</i>

35:09.890 --> 35:11.021
<i>♪</i>

35:11.065 --> 35:12.762
- Here, give me the gun!

35:12.806 --> 35:18.203
<i>♪</i>

35:25.384 --> 35:27.603
Pretty good with that thing.

35:27.647 --> 35:34.654
<i>♪</i>

35:35.350 --> 35:38.179
We're not just
gonna kill you, Lois.

35:38.223 --> 35:40.573
He wanted you to suffer first.

35:40.616 --> 35:47.667
<i>♪</i>

35:53.716 --> 35:55.762
- They're gone.

36:03.770 --> 36:07.687
<i>♪</i>

36:07.730 --> 36:09.428
- Better than ice,

36:09.471 --> 36:12.648
unless that was a lie
you told me when I was a kid.

36:12.692 --> 36:15.477
- Only way I could get you
to do it.

36:15.521 --> 36:17.871
We sure went through
our fair share of frozen peas,

36:17.914 --> 36:18.959
didn't we?

36:19.002 --> 36:20.439
God, even as a kid,

36:20.482 --> 36:22.919
you were always coming home
bruised up.

36:22.963 --> 36:26.488
<i>♪</i>

36:26.532 --> 36:28.577
I was never there to keep you
from getting them though,

36:28.621 --> 36:30.753
was I?

36:30.797 --> 36:33.234
- Dad.
- It's true.

36:33.278 --> 36:37.934
Everything you said is true.

36:37.978 --> 36:40.850
I wasn't the best father.

36:40.894 --> 36:45.594
I was gone a lot,

36:45.638 --> 36:49.946
and I wasn't there to protect
you the way a parent should.

36:49.990 --> 36:54.037
<i>♪</i>

36:54.081 --> 36:57.519
- You were tonight.

36:57.563 --> 36:59.869
- Couldn't let them
hurt my grandson.

37:03.308 --> 37:05.962
Or my little girl.

37:13.796 --> 37:17.147
Lois, we're gonna stay here
till this is over.

37:17.191 --> 37:19.237
As of now,

37:19.280 --> 37:22.936
you, the boys,
Clark, Smallville,

37:22.979 --> 37:24.807
that's my priority.

37:24.851 --> 37:27.114
- Good.

37:27.157 --> 37:31.553
'Cause that war John Henry Irons
was talking about,

37:31.597 --> 37:34.252
I think it's about to happen.

37:36.166 --> 37:38.430
- Think Mom's gonna let you
keep those solar weapons now?

37:38.473 --> 37:40.388
- I don't know.

37:40.432 --> 37:43.086
I mean, they're pretty much the
only reason we're alive, so...

37:43.130 --> 37:46.046
- It'd suck to come home and
find out I was an only child.

37:48.614 --> 37:50.442
- Yeah.

37:50.485 --> 37:52.966
So...

37:53.009 --> 37:56.709
so you're just, like, fine now?

37:56.752 --> 38:00.060
- Yeah, other than ice breath.

38:00.103 --> 38:01.888
- So you have that now for good,
or what?

38:01.931 --> 38:04.978
- Think so.
- What's that feel like?

38:05.021 --> 38:06.980
- Like having a piece
of wintergreen gum

38:07.023 --> 38:08.982
in your mouth at all times.

38:09.025 --> 38:10.418
- Nice.

38:10.462 --> 38:13.813
- I can't believe
what happened.

38:13.856 --> 38:17.338
Avery Phan's mom
and Mr. Cushing?

38:17.382 --> 38:18.644
- Right, but it wasn't them,
you know?

38:18.687 --> 38:21.516
They were super,
super brainwashed.

38:21.560 --> 38:24.214
I think Grandpa's sending
a few people

38:24.258 --> 38:26.260
to go look for 'em both.

38:28.044 --> 38:32.222
- What are they gonna
tell Sarah?

38:32.266 --> 38:33.963
- I don't know.

38:34.007 --> 38:36.662
<i>♪</i>

38:39.142 --> 38:43.321
<i>♪</i>

38:44.539 --> 38:48.064
- My God, what happened?
- Are you drunk?

38:48.108 --> 38:50.458
- No.
- Honey, could you excuse us?

38:50.502 --> 38:51.938
- Mom--
- Please?

38:51.981 --> 38:54.375
I need to speak
to your father alone.

38:56.508 --> 38:59.815
- Sure.

38:59.859 --> 39:02.775
- Are you?
- No.

39:02.818 --> 39:07.345
No, look, I told you
I am done with all that.

39:07.388 --> 39:09.608
I'm trying to improve myself,
Lana.

39:09.651 --> 39:11.392
I really am,

39:11.436 --> 39:13.916
but something happened to me
tonight.

39:13.960 --> 39:16.702
I was at the performance,

39:16.745 --> 39:19.444
and we were talking to Sarah,

39:19.487 --> 39:21.924
and then I blacked out.

39:21.968 --> 39:24.187
Next thing you know, I'm out
in the middle of a field

39:24.231 --> 39:26.799
somewhere outside of town,
and my ribs--

39:26.842 --> 39:29.845
my ribs are hurting, and I
don't know how I got there.

39:29.889 --> 39:33.371
I don't know what's going on--
what?

39:34.720 --> 39:38.376
- The steps you're taking
to improve yourself--

39:38.419 --> 39:41.291
did Morgan Edge
make you an offer?

39:44.338 --> 39:51.389
<i>♪</i>

40:02.008 --> 40:04.402
- How can I help you?

40:04.445 --> 40:06.578
- I want to be my best self.

40:06.621 --> 40:09.276
I wanted to be better

40:09.319 --> 40:13.062
for you and for our girls,
babe.

40:19.329 --> 40:20.461
- Hey, Chrissy.

40:20.505 --> 40:22.202
<i>- You said if we kept digging,</i>

40:22.245 --> 40:23.595
<i>the answer would present
itself, and honestly,</i>

40:23.638 --> 40:25.074
for a while I thought
you were nuts

40:25.118 --> 40:26.467
'cause nothing new
was coming to light,

40:26.511 --> 40:27.860
but then I got back
all the research

40:27.903 --> 40:29.775
<i>on the powered people
we know,</i>

40:29.818 --> 40:31.951
<i>and I found this little nugget
that means something.</i>

40:31.994 --> 40:34.519
I just don't know what yet
but thought your big brain

40:34.562 --> 40:35.998
might be able
to connect the dots.

40:36.042 --> 40:37.739
- Chrissy, what are you
talking about?

40:37.783 --> 40:41.221
- Irma Sayres
and David Fuglestad.

40:41.264 --> 40:42.657
- Who?

40:42.701 --> 40:46.182
- Leslie Larr
and motel attacker guy.

40:46.226 --> 40:48.881
- Leslie Larr's real name
is Irma Sayres?

40:48.924 --> 40:51.405
- Mm-hmm, and the guy
is David Fuglestad,

40:51.449 --> 40:53.059
<i>and guess what?</i>

40:53.102 --> 40:56.889
I found out they're both
originally from Smallville.

40:56.932 --> 40:59.413
<i>♪</i>

40:59.457 --> 41:01.328
- Derek Powell's
from New Carthage.

41:01.371 --> 41:03.243
Reno Rosetti's from Metropolis.

41:03.286 --> 41:06.551
- David Fuglestad and
Leslie Larr are from Smallville.

41:06.594 --> 41:08.335
- When Derek Powell
killed himself,

41:08.378 --> 41:10.250
what did he say to you?

41:10.293 --> 41:13.209
- That he was already dead.
- And his powers were fritzing.

41:13.253 --> 41:15.429
- Yeah, just like Rosetti's.

41:15.473 --> 41:16.909
That didn't happen
when I fought David.

41:16.952 --> 41:19.128
- And it didn't happen
with Leslie.

41:19.172 --> 41:23.393
<i>♪</i>

41:23.437 --> 41:25.091
- When I landed here,

41:25.134 --> 41:26.440
there were meteor showers
all over the world

41:26.484 --> 41:28.355
for an entire week.

41:28.398 --> 41:30.270
- Right, remnants of Krypton.
That's why there's kryptonite.

41:30.313 --> 41:32.185
- Right,
every form of kryptonite,

41:32.228 --> 41:35.057
and the kind that landed here
is buried in the mines.

41:35.101 --> 41:37.016
- Was X-Kryptonite.

41:37.059 --> 41:39.279
So the only place in the world
that has X-Kryptonite

41:39.322 --> 41:41.237
is also the only place
that has people

41:41.281 --> 41:44.197
who've been exposed to it long
enough to accept its effects.

41:44.240 --> 41:48.070
- Like Tag Harris.

41:48.114 --> 41:50.290
It's not Smallville Edge needs
to build his army.

41:50.333 --> 41:53.641
- It's the people.

41:57.079 --> 41:59.038
What?

41:59.081 --> 42:00.909
- It's your ELT.

42:00.953 --> 42:02.563
<i>♪</i>

42:02.607 --> 42:04.565
- Edge.

42:04.609 --> 42:11.616
<i>♪</i>

42:14.575 --> 42:16.751
- I'm glad you came.

42:16.795 --> 42:19.188
- Everything you're doing
is gonna stop.

42:19.232 --> 42:21.321
- That's exactly what
your friend Lois Lane

42:21.364 --> 42:23.105
keeps saying to me.

42:23.149 --> 42:26.805
You can't make that happen
any more than she can.

42:26.848 --> 42:33.899
<i>♪</i>

42:37.642 --> 42:40.122
- Did you really think
I'd be giving people powers

42:40.166 --> 42:42.255
without having them myself?

42:42.298 --> 42:46.259
You see, I got mine
the same time you did, Kal-El,

42:46.302 --> 42:48.000
when I arrived on this planet.

42:48.043 --> 42:49.915
- When you arrived?

42:49.958 --> 42:53.048
<i>♪</i>

42:53.092 --> 42:56.008
- I think it's time you learned
the truth about who I am

42:56.051 --> 42:59.838
and where I'm really from,

42:59.881 --> 43:02.275
brother.

43:02.318 --> 43:06.801
<i>♪</i>

43:29.650 --> 43:32.653
- Greg, move your head.
